div.p:
To His Excellency
WILLIAM Lord CRAVEN, Palatine;
The most Noble, HENRY Duke of BEAUFORT;
The Right Honble JOHN Lord CARTERET;
The Honble MAURICE ASHLEY, Esq;
Sir JOHN COLLETON, Baronet,
JOHN DANSON, Esq;
And the rest of the True and absolute
LORDS-PROPRIETORS
OF THE
Province of Carolina in America. MY LORDS,

Of Rats we have two sorts; the House-Rat, as in Europe;
                    and the Marsh-Rat, which differs very much from the other, being more hairy, and
                    has several other Distinctions, too long here to name.

The Belly of the first is of a Carnation or Pink Colour; his Back a dirty brown;
                    they are large, but have not much Venom in them, as ever I learnt. The next is a large Snake, of a brown Dirt Colour, and always abides
                    in the Marshes.

Crampois is a large Fish, and by some accounted a young Whale; but it is not so;
                    neither is it-more-than twenty five or thirty Foot long. They spout as the Whale
                    does, and when taken yield good Oil.

Another Game is managed with a Batoon and a Ball, and resembles our Trap-ball;
                    besides, several Nations have several Games and Pastimes, which are not used by
                    others.
